name: Andhra Pradesh Engineering, Agriculture and Medical Councils (AP EAMCET)

details.Application Process: The application process is typically open from January to February of each year.
details.Examination Details: The examination is usually held in April of each year.
details.Eligibility Criteria: The eligibility criteria for AP EAMCET include qualifying marks in the entrance test and meeting certain academic requirements.
details.Exam Format: The exam format typically includes multiple-choice questions and short-answer questions.
details.Test Centers: The test centers are usually located in various cities across Andhra Pradesh, including Hyderabad, Guntur, and Vijayawada.

details.description: Engineering, Agriculture and Pharmacy Common Entrance Test conducted by Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University Kakinada.
details.correction_instructions: Corrections related to CATEGORY-1 items will be done at CONVENER, AP EAPCET-2024 Office, subject to thorough Verification of the Valid Documents and Approval by the Committee. Corrections related to CATEGORY-2 in the Filled in Online Application Form should be done by the candidate during the permitted period (04.05.2024 to 06.05.2024) only.
